ZH: 这道菜需要一点盐才能更美味。
EN: This dish needs a little salt to taste better.

ZH: 我们家买的盐是从海边产的。
EN: The salt that we buy is from the seaside.

ZH: 盐是一种调味料，可以增加食物的美味。
EN: Salt is a seasoning that can enhance the flavor of food.

ZH: 我建议你少放盐，注意健康。
EN: I suggest you use less salt and pay attention to your health.

ZH: 煮饭时加一点盐，可以使米饭更香。
EN: Adding a little salt when cooking rice can make it more fragrant.

ZH: 盐和糖是两种截然不同的食物调味品。
EN: Salt and sugar are two completely different food seasonings.

ZH: 这种盐比普通盐更有营养价值。
EN: This salt is more nutritious than regular salt.

ZH: 盐的主要成分是氯化钠。
EN: The main component of salt is sodium chloride.

ZH: 烹调时要注意不要放太多盐。
EN: When cooking, be careful not to put too much salt.

ZH: 红烧肉需要酱油和盐来调味。
EN: Braised pork requires soy sauce and salt for seasoning.

ZH: 这种盐是天然晒制的，没有添加任何化学物质。
EN: This salt is naturally sun-dried and contains no added chemicals.

ZH: 糖盐融合在一起，增加了菜肴的甜咸口感。
EN: Sugar and salt blend together, enhancing the sweet and salty taste of the dish.

ZH: 盐在烹饪中扮演着非常重要的角色。
EN: Salt plays a very important role in cooking.

ZH: 这包盐的价钱比上个月贵了。
EN: The price of this pack of salt is higher than last month.

ZH: 在炎热的夏天，人们会更容易流失体内的盐分。
EN: In hot summer days, people are more likely to lose salt from their bodies.

ZH: 盐被广泛用于食品加工和腌制食物。
EN: Salt is widely used in food processing and food preservation.

ZH: 烧烤食物时撒一点盐，会更有风味。
EN: Sprinkling a little salt on grilled food adds more flavor.

ZH: 盐分也是组成海水的重要成分之一。
EN: Salt is also one of the important components of seawater.

ZH: 老人胃口不好，需要食品中少盐。
EN: Elderly people with poor appetite need less salt in their food.
